{"ts": "2026-06-12T11:24:58.000Z", "event": "planner", "msg": "L3 task decomposition", "agent": "planner-l3", "tokens_in": 1277, "tokens_out": 23526, "elapsed_ms": 220087, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Level 3 Planner. Decompose the user task into subtasks for dynamic agent creation.\n\nOutput JSON:\n{{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {{\"task_id\": \"short-name\", \"description\": \"What this worker must produce — ALWAYS include the user's exact request at the top\"}}\n  ]\n}}\n\n## Critical Rules\n- Each subtask description MUST begin with \"USER REQUEST: <exact user task text>\" — this prevents worker hallucination\n- Each subtask must be focused, self-contained, with explicit output file names\n- Never create duplicate task_ids — each worker name must be unique\n- For simple tasks, 3-4 subtasks; for complex tasks, 4-6\n- Always include a \"tester\" as the FINAL subtask — running test_report.json validation\n- Specify exact file names each worker must produce (e.g. \"Write to styles.css\", \"Write to app.js\")\n- Workers receive NO prior context beyond their subtask description — be thorough in the description\n- Output ONLY the JSON object — no markdown fences, no extra text\n\n## Specialty\nfrontend\n\n## User Request\nBuild a personal portfolio page for Aymen, a Python Backend Developer. Deliver as index.html, styles.css, app.js. USE generate_image for visual assets.\n\n## SECTION ANIMATIONS (CRITICAL - every section must animate)\n- ALL sections start hidden: opacity:0, transform:translateY(40px)\n- When scrolled into view, animate to: opacity:1, translateY:0 (0.6s ease-out)\n- Hero animates on page load, other sections on scroll (IntersectionObserver 15%)\n- Cards within sections stagger: each card 150ms apart\n- DO NOT skip opacity:0 - both transform AND opacity must animate\n\n## SECTIONS\n\n### Hero\n- Headline \"Aymen - Backend Developer\" in large gradient text\n- Subheadline \"Building robust APIs and scalable systems with Python, FastAPI & PostgreSQL\"\n- Two CTA buttons: \"View Projects\" and \"Contact Me\"\n- Animated CSS gradient background that slowly shifts\n- generate_image: create a tech-themed abstract profile avatar/icon\n\n### Skills (animated progress bars)\n- Python/FastAPI 95%, PostgreSQL/SQLAlchemy 90%, Docker/K8s 85%, Redis/Celery 80%, AWS/GCP 75%\n- Bars fill from 0 to target on scroll (requestAnimationFrame ease-out over 1.5s)\n- Show percentage number next to each bar\n\n### Projects (3 cards with IMAGES)\n- \"Orcheeos API\" - Multi-agent LLM orchestration backend (FastAPI, LangGraph). generate_image: server/API tech thumbnail\n- \"DataFlow Engine\" - Real-time pipeline processing 1M events/day (Python, Redis, Docker). generate_image: data-flow thumbnail\n- \"Auth Microservice\" - OAuth2/JWT authentication service (FastAPI, PostgreSQL, Redis). generate_image: security thumbnail\n- Cards have hover lift + shadow effect\n\n### Experience Timeline\n- 2024-Present: Senior Backend Dev at TechCorp - \"Led migration to microservices, 10x throughput\"\n- 2022-2024: Backend Dev at StartupX - \"Built REST APIs serving 500K daily users\"\n- 2020-2022: Junior Dev at WebAgency - \"Developed 15+ client projects with Django/FastAPI\"\n- Vertical timeline: left border line + animated dots on scroll\n\n### Contact\n- Name, Email, Message - real-time validation, shake animation on error\n- Valid: show green toast \"Message sent!\" that fades after 3s\n- localStorage persistence\n\n### Footer\n- GitHub, LinkedIn, Twitter emoji links. Copyright \"Aymen\"\n\n## THEME: dark default (#0f172a), light toggle with localStorage, 0.3s transitions\n\nFor frontend tasks, you MUST follow these constraints:\n- Always include a final \"integration\" subtask that merges all content/fragments into index.html\n- Always include a \"tester\" subtask as the VERY LAST subtask\n- Good decomposition: [content, html_structure, styling, interactivity, integration, tester]\n- Bad decomposition: [hero_builder, features_builder, cta_builder] — these create standalone pages\n- Each subtask description MUST include the user's verbatim request text at the top\n- Section subtasks produce content fragments into shared files, NOT standalone HTML files\n- The pipeline produces ONE web page: index.html + styles.css + app.js\n\n## CSS-HTML Coordination\n- The HTML worker MUST add semantic CSS classes to every major section (class=\"hero\", class=\"features\", class=\"cta\", class=\"footer\" etc.)\n- The styling worker's subtask MUST say: \"read_file('index.html') FIRST. Write CSS selectors matching the EXACT classes/IDs/elements found in index.html. Do NOT invent new class names.\"\n- The integration subtask MUST include: \"1) read index.html to see classes used, 2) read content.txt for real text, 3) read styles.css to see which classes need to exist, 4) write_file('index.html') with content injected AND missing CSS classes added, 5) read_file('index.html') to verify.\"\n\n## Token Efficiency\n- Each worker≈100K token budget limit for the entire pipeline, plan your decomposition and worker complexity accordingly\n- Avoid micro-workers that do trivial tasks — combine related work into fewer, more substantial workers\n- The CSS/styling worker should NOT call validate_css more than 3 times total", "meta": {}}
{"ts": "2026-06-12T11:27:50.000Z", "event": "agent_creator", "msg": "Agent Creator L3 — generating workers", "agent": "agent-creator-l3", "tokens_in": 9093, "tokens_out": 16512, "elapsed_ms": 171892, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Advanced Agent Creator (Level 3 — Fully Autonomous). Your role: create worker agents from scratch with custom system instructions, tools, and dynamic code tools.\n\n## Available Tools\nThe tool menu for this specialty:\n[\"read_file\", \"write_file\", \"list_files\", \"run_command\", \"render_html_screenshot\", \"render_html_file_screenshot\", \"validate_html\", \"validate_css\", \"read_image\", \"generate_image\"]\n\n## Task Plan\nThe planner has decomposed the task into subtasks:\n{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"content_and_assets\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a personal portfolio page for Aymen, a Python Backend Developer. Deliver as index.html, styles.css, app.js. USE generate_image for visual assets.\\n\\n## SECTION ANIMATIONS (CRITICAL - every section must animate)\\n- ALL sections start hidden: opacity:0, transform:translateY(40px)\\n- When scrolled into view, animate to: opacity:1, translateY:0 (0.6s ease-out)\\n- Hero animates on page load, other sections on scroll (IntersectionObserver 15%)\\n- Cards within sections stagger: each card 150ms apart\\n- DO NOT skip opacity:0 - both transform AND opacity must animate\\n\\n## SECTIONS\\n\\n### Hero\\n- Headline \\\"Aymen - Backend Developer\\\" in large gradient text\\n- Subheadline \\\"Building robust APIs and scalable systems with Python, FastAPI & PostgreSQL\\\"\\n- Two CTA buttons: \\\"View Projects\\\" and \\\"Contact Me\\\"\\n- Animated CSS gradient background that slowly shifts\\n- generate_image: create a tech-themed abstract profile avatar/icon\\n\\n### Skills (animated progress bars)\\n- Python/FastAPI 95%, PostgreSQL/SQLAlchemy 90%, Docker/K8s 85%, Redis/Celery 80%, AWS/GCP 75%\\n- Bars fill from 0 to target on scroll (requestAnimationFrame ease-out over 1.5s)\\n- Show percentage number next to each bar\\n\\n### Projects (3 cards with IMAGES)\\n- \\\"Orcheeos API\\\" - Multi-agent LLM orchestration backend (FastAPI, LangGraph). generate_image: server/API tech thumbnail\\n- \\\"DataFlow Engine\\\" - Real-time pipeline processing 1M events/day (Python, Redis, Docker). generate_image: data-flow thumbnail\\n- \\\"Auth Microservice\\\" - OAuth2/JWT authentication service (FastAPI, PostgreSQL, Redis). generate_image: security thumbnail\\n- Cards have hover lift + shadow effect\\n\\n### Experience Timeline\\n- 2024-Present: Senior Backend Dev at TechCorp - \\\"Led migration to microservices, 10x throughput\\\"\\n- 2022-2024: Backend Dev at StartupX - \\\"Built REST APIs serving 500K daily users\\\"\\n- 2020-2022: Junior Dev at WebAgency - \\\"Developed 15+ client projects with Django/FastAPI\\\"\\n- Vertical timeline: left border line + animated dots on scroll\\n\\n### Contact\\n- Name, Email, Message - real-time validation, shake animation on error\\n- Valid: show green toast \\\"Message sent!\\\" that fades after 3s\\n- localStorage persistence\\n\\n### Footer\\n- GitHub, LinkedIn, Twitter emoji links. Copyright \\\"Aymen\\\"\\n\\n## THEME: dark default (#0f172a), light toggle with localStorage, 0.3s transitions\\n\\nFor frontend tasks, you MUST follow these constraints:\\n- Always include a final \\\"integration\\\" subtask that merges all content/fragments into index.html\\n- Always include a \\\"tester\\\" subtask as the VERY LAST subtask\\n- Good decomposition: [content, html_structure, styling, interactivity, integration, tester]\\n- Bad decomposition: [hero_builder, features_builder, cta_builder] \\u2014 these create standalone pages\\n- Each subtask description MUST include the user's verbatim request text at the top\\n- Section subtasks produce content fragments into shared files, NOT standalone HTML files\\n- The pipeline produces ONE web page: index.html + styles.css + app.js\\n\\n## CSS-HTML Coordination\\n- The HTML worker MUST add semantic CSS classes to every major section (class=\\\"hero\\\", class=\\\"features\\\", class=\\\"cta\\\", class=\\\"footer\\\" etc.)\\n- The styling worker's subtask MUST say: \\\"read_file('index.html') FIRST. Write CSS selectors matching the EXACT classes/IDs/elements found in index.html. Do NOT invent new class names.\\\"\\n- The integration subtask MUST include: \\\"1) read index.html to see classes used, 2) read content.txt for real text, 3) read styles.css to see which classes need to exist, 4) write_file('index.html') with content injected AND missing CSS classes added, 5) read_file('index.html') to verify.\\\"\\n\\n## Token Efficiency\\n- Each worker\\u2248100K token budget limit for the entire pipeline, plan your decomposition and worker complexity accordingly\\n- Avoid micro-workers that do trivial tasks \\u2014 combine related work into fewer, more substantial workers\\n- The CSS/styling worker should NOT call validate_css more than 3 times total\\n\\nYou are the content and assets specialist. You must:\\n1. Write all textual content to content.json. Include: hero headline, subheadline, button texts; skills array with name and percentage; projects array with title, description, tech stack; experience array with date, title, company, description; contact labels; footer links and copyright. Use exact data from the user request.\\n2. Use the generate_image tool to create four images exactly as described: a) tech_avatar.png: tech-themed abstract profile avatar/icon; b) orcheeos_api.png: server/API tech thumbnail; c) dataflow_engine.png: data-flow thumbnail; d) auth_microservice.png: security thumbnail. Save them to a folder named 'images'. After generating, create images.json mapping logical names (avatar, project1, project2, project3) to the file paths.\\nThe generated images and content will be used by later workers. Write content.json and images.json.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"html_structure\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a personal portfolio page for Aymen, a Python Backend Developer. Deliver as index.html, styles.css, app.js. USE generate_image for visual assets.\\n\\n## SECTION ANIMATIONS (CRITICAL - every section must animate)\\n- ALL sections start hidden: opacity:0, transform:translateY(40px)\\n- When scrolled into view, animate to: opacity:1, translateY:0 (0.6s ease-out)\\n- Hero animates on page load, other sections on scroll (IntersectionObserver 15%)\\n- Cards within sections stagger: each card 150ms apart\\n- DO NOT skip opacity:0 - both transform AND opacity must animate\\n\\n## SECTIONS\\n\\n### Hero\\n- Headline \\\"Aymen - Backend Developer\\\" in large gradient text\\n- Subheadline \\\"Building robust APIs and scalable systems with Python, FastAPI & PostgreSQL\\\"\\n- Two CTA buttons: \\\"View Projects\\\" and \\\"Contact Me\\\"\\n- Animated CSS gradient background that slowly shifts\\n- generate_image: create a tech-themed abstract profile avatar/icon\\n\\n### Skills (animated progress bars)\\n- Python/FastAPI 95%, PostgreSQL/SQLAlchemy 90%, Docker/K8s 85%, Redis/Celery 80%, AWS/GCP 75%\\n- Bars fill from 0 to target on scroll (requestAnimationFrame ease-out over 1.5s)\\n- Show percentage number next to each bar\\n\\n### Projects (3 cards with IMAGES)\\n- \\\"Orcheeos API\\\" - Multi-agent LLM orchestration backend (FastAPI, LangGraph). generate_image: server/API tech thumbnail\\n- \\\"DataFlow Engine\\\" - Real-time pipeline processing 1M events/day (Python, Redis, Docker). generate_image: data-flow thumbnail\\n- \\\"Auth Microservice\\\" - OAuth2/JWT authentication service (FastAPI, PostgreSQL, Redis). generate_image: security thumbnail\\n- Cards have hover lift + shadow effect\\n\\n### Experience Timeline\\n- 2024-Present: Senior Backend Dev at TechCorp - \\\"Led migration to microservices, 10x throughput\\\"\\n- 2022-2024: Backend Dev at StartupX - \\\"Built REST APIs serving 500K daily users\\\"\\n- 2020-2022: Junior Dev at WebAgency - \\\"Developed 15+ client projects with Django/FastAPI\\\"\\n- Vertical timeline: left border line + animated dots on scroll\\n\\n### Contact\\n- Name, Email, Message - real-time validation, shake animation on error\\n- Valid: show green toast \\\"Message sent!\\\" that fades after 3s\\n- localStorage persistence\\n\\n### Footer\\n- GitHub, LinkedIn, Twitter emoji links. Copyright \\\"Aymen\\\"\\n\\n## THEME: dark default (#0f172a), light toggle with localStorage, 0.3s transitions\\n\\nFor frontend tasks, you MUST follow these constraints:\\n- Always include a final \\\"integration\\\" subtask that merges all content/fragments into index.html\\n- Always include a \\\"tester\\\" subtask as the VERY LAST subtask\\n- Good decomposition: [content, html_structure, styling, interactivity, integration, tester]\\n- Bad decomposition: [hero_builder, features_builder, cta_builder] \\u2014 these create standalone pages\\n- Each subtask description MUST include the user's verbatim request text at the top\\n- Section subtasks produce content fragments into shared files, NOT standalone HTML files\\n- The pipeline produces ONE web page: index.html + styles.css + app.js\\n\\n## CSS-HTML Coordination\\n- The HTML worker MUST add semantic CSS classes to every major section (class=\\\"hero\\\", class=\\\"features\\\", class=\\\"cta\\\", class=\\\"footer\\\" etc.)\\n- The styling worker's subtask MUST say: \\\"read_file('index.html') FIRST. Write CSS selectors matching the EXACT classes/IDs/elements found in index.html. Do NOT invent new class names.\\\"\\n- The integration subtask MUST include: \\\"1) read index.html to see classes used, 2) read content.txt for real text, 3) read styles.css to see which classes need to exist, 4) write_file('index.html') with content injected AND missing CSS classes added, 5) read_file('index.html') to verify.\\\"\\n\\n## Token Efficiency\\n- Each worker\\u2248100K token budget limit for the entire pipeline, plan your decomposition and worker complexity accordingly\\n- Avoid micro-workers that do trivial tasks \\u2014 combine related work into fewer, more substantial workers\\n- The CSS/styling worker should NOT call validate_css more than 3 times total\\n\\nYou are the HTML structure builder. Write to index.html a complete, valid HTML5 document with all required sections. Each section must have a semantic class: <header class=\\\"hero\\\">, <section class=\\\"skills\\\">, <section class=\\\"projects\\\">, <section class=\\\"experience\\\">, <section class=\\\"contact\\\">, <footer class=\\\"footer\\\">. Also include a <button class=\\\"theme-toggle\\\"> for dark/light mode. Use placeholders for all textual content using double curly braces (e.g., {{hero.headline}}). For images, set src to '' and add a data attribute 'data-img' indicating which image to use (e.g., data-img=\\\"avatar\\\"). Link to styles.css in <head> and app.js before </body>. Include meta viewport. Ensure the structure matches user requirements (hero with headline, subheadline, two buttons; skills section with progress bars; projects with 3 cards each having image, title, description; experience with vertical timeline; contact form with inputs; footer with links). This file will later be populated with real content and images.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"styling\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a personal portfolio page for Aymen, a Python Backend Developer. Deliver as index.html, styles.css, app.js. USE generate_image for visual assets.\\n\\n## SECTION ANIMATIONS (CRITICAL - every section must animate)\\n- ALL sections start hidden: opacity:0, transform:translateY(40px)\\n- When scrolled into view, animate to: opacity:1, translateY:0 (0.6s ease-out)\\n- Hero animates on page load, other sections on scroll (IntersectionObserver 15%)\\n- Cards within sections stagger: each card 150ms apart\\n- DO NOT skip opacity:0 - both transform AND opacity must animate\\n\\n## SECTIONS\\n\\n### Hero\\n- Headline \\\"Aymen - Backend Developer\\\" in large gradient text\\n- Subheadline \\\"Building robust APIs and scalable systems with Python, FastAPI & PostgreSQL\\\"\\n- Two CTA buttons: \\\"View Projects\\\" and \\\"Contact Me\\\"\\n- Animated CSS gradient background that slowly shifts\\n- generate_image: create a tech-themed abstract profile avatar/icon\\n\\n### Skills (animated progress bars)\\n- Python/FastAPI 95%, PostgreSQL/SQLAlchemy 90%, Docker/K8s 85%, Redis/Celery 80%, AWS/GCP 75%\\n- Bars fill from 0 to target on scroll (requestAnimationFrame ease-out over 1.5s)\\n- Show percentage number next to each bar\\n\\n### Projects (3 cards with IMAGES)\\n- \\\"Orcheeos API\\\" - Multi-agent LLM orchestration backend (FastAPI, LangGraph). generate_image: server/API tech thumbnail\\n- \\\"DataFlow Engine\\\" - Real-time pipeline processing 1M events/day (Python, Redis, Docker). generate_image: data-flow thumbnail\\n- \\\"Auth Microservice\\\" - OAuth2/JWT authentication service (FastAPI, PostgreSQL, Redis). generate_image: security thumbnail\\n- Cards have hover lift + shadow effect\\n\\n### Experience Timeline\\n- 2024-Present: Senior Backend Dev at TechCorp - \\\"Led migration to microservices, 10x throughput\\\"\\n- 2022-2024: Backend Dev at StartupX - \\\"Built REST APIs serving 500K daily users\\\"\\n- 2020-2022: Junior Dev at WebAgency - \\\"Developed 15+ client projects with Django/FastAPI\\\"\\n- Vertical timeline: left border line + animated dots on scroll\\n\\n### Contact\\n- Name, Email, Message - real-time validation, shake animation on error\\n- Valid: show green toast \\\"Message sent!\\\" that fades after 3s\\n- localStorage persistence\\n\\n### Footer\\n- GitHub, LinkedIn, Twitter emoji links. Copyright \\\"Aymen\\\"\\n\\n## THEME: dark default (#0f172a), light toggle with localStorage, 0.3s transitions\\n\\nFor frontend tasks, you MUST follow these constraints:\\n- Always include a final \\\"integration\\\" subtask that merges all content/fragments into index.html\\n- Always include a \\\"tester\\\" subtask as the VERY LAST subtask\\n- Good decomposition: [content, html_structure, styling, interactivity, integration, tester]\\n- Bad decomposition: [hero_builder, features_builder, cta_builder] \\u2014 these create standalone pages\\n- Each subtask description MUST include the user's verbatim request text at the top\\n- Section subtasks produce content fragments into shared files, NOT standalone HTML files\\n- The pipeline produces ONE web page: index.html + styles.css + app.js\\n\\n## CSS-HTML Coordination\\n- The HTML worker MUST add semantic CSS classes to every major section (class=\\\"hero\\\", class=\\\"features\\\", class=\\\"cta\\\", class=\\\"footer\\\" etc.)\\n- The styling worker's subtask MUST say: \\\"read_file('index.html') FIRST. Write CSS selectors matching the EXACT classes/IDs/elements found in index.html. Do NOT invent new class names.\\\"\\n- The integration subtask MUST include: \\\"1) read index.html to see classes used, 2) read content.txt for real text, 3) read styles.css to see which classes need to exist, 4) write_file('index.html') with content injected AND missing CSS classes added, 5) read_file('index.html') to verify.\\\"\\n\\n## Token Efficiency\\n- Each worker\\u2248100K token budget limit for the entire pipeline, plan your decomposition and worker complexity accordingly\\n- Avoid micro-workers that do trivial tasks \\u2014 combine related work into fewer, more substantial workers\\n- The CSS/styling worker should NOT call validate_css more than 3 times total\\n\\nYou are the CSS styling worker. FIRST, read_file('index.html') to exactly understand the classes and structure. Then write to styles.css. Implement all styles according to the user requirements:\\n- Dark theme default (#0f172a background, light text). Light theme toggle via body.light-mode with 0.3s transitions on background and color.\\n- Section animations: ALL sections must start with opacity:0; transform: translateY(40px). When scrolled into view, they should get class 'visible' that transitions to opacity:1; transform: none; with 0.6s ease-out.\\n- Hero: large gradient text for headline, animated CSS gradient background, CTA buttons styled.\\n- Skills: .progress-bar container, .progress-bar-fill with width 0 (animated by JS), show .percentage span.\\n- Projects: .project-card with hover lift (translateY(-5px)) and box-shadow increase.\\n- Experience: vertical timeline with left border line and .timeline-dot animated on scroll.\\n- Contact: form validation styles, .shake animation, .toast green message that fades.\\n- Footer styling.\\n- Responsive design with at least one breakpoint for mobile.\\nDo NOT invent new class names; use exactly the classes found in index.html. If a necessary class is missing from index.html, note it for the integration step. Write all CSS rules.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"interactivity\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a personal portfolio page for Aymen, a Python Backend Developer. Deliver as index.html, styles.css, app.js. USE generate_image for visual assets.\\n\\n## SECTION ANIMATIONS (CRITICAL - every section must animate)\\n- ALL sections start hidden: opacity:0, transform:translateY(40px)\\n- When scrolled into view, animate to: opacity:1, translateY:0 (0.6s ease-out)\\n- Hero animates on page load, other sections on scroll (IntersectionObserver 15%)\\n- Cards within sections stagger: each card 150ms apart\\n- DO NOT skip opacity:0 - both transform AND opacity must animate\\n\\n## SECTIONS\\n\\n### Hero\\n- Headline \\\"Aymen - Backend Developer\\\" in large gradient text\\n- Subheadline \\\"Building robust APIs and scalable systems with Python, FastAPI & PostgreSQL\\\"\\n- Two CTA buttons: \\\"View Projects\\\" and \\\"Contact Me\\\"\\n- Animated CSS gradient background that slowly shifts\\n- generate_image: create a tech-themed abstract profile avatar/icon\\n\\n### Skills (animated progress bars)\\n- Python/FastAPI 95%, PostgreSQL/SQLAlchemy 90%, Docker/K8s 85%, Redis/Celery 80%, AWS/GCP 75%\\n- Bars fill from 0 to target on scroll (requestAnimationFrame ease-out over 1.5s)\\n- Show percentage number next to each bar\\n\\n### Projects (3 cards with IMAGES)\\n- \\\"Orcheeos API\\\" - Multi-agent LLM orchestration backend (FastAPI, LangGraph). generate_image: server/API tech thumbnail\\n- \\\"DataFlow Engine\\\" - Real-time pipeline processing 1M events/day (Python, Redis, Docker). generate_image: data-flow thumbnail\\n- \\\"Auth Microservice\\\" - OAuth2/JWT authentication service (FastAPI, PostgreSQL, Redis). generate_image: security thumbnail\\n- Cards have hover lift + shadow effect\\n\\n### Experience Timeline\\n- 2024-Present: Senior Backend Dev at TechCorp - \\\"Led migration to microservices, 10x throughput\\\"\\n- 2022-2024: Backend Dev at StartupX - \\\"Built REST APIs serving 500K daily users\\\"\\n- 2020-2022: Junior Dev at WebAgency - \\\"Developed 15+ client projects with Django/FastAPI\\\"\\n- Vertical timeline: left border line + animated dots on scroll\\n\\n### Contact\\n- Name, Email, Message - real-time validation, shake animation on error\\n- Valid: show green toast \\\"Message sent!\\\" that fades after 3s\\n- localStorage persistence\\n\\n### Footer\\n- GitHub, LinkedIn, Twitter emoji links. Copyright \\\"Aymen\\\"\\n\\n## THEME: dark default (#0f172a), light toggle with localStorage, 0.3s transitions\\n\\nFor frontend tasks, you MUST follow these constraints:\\n- Always include a final \\\"integration\\\" subtask that merges all content/fragments into index.html\\n- Always include a \\\"tester\\\" subtask as the VERY LAST subtask\\n- Good decomposition: [content, html_structure, styling, interactivity, integration, tester]\\n- Bad decomposition: [hero_builder, features_builder, cta_builder] \\u2014 these create standalone pages\\n- Each subtask description MUST include the user's verbatim request text at the top\\n- Section subtasks produce content fragments into shared files, NOT standalone HTML files\\n- The pipeline produces ONE web page: index.html + styles.css + app.js\\n\\n## CSS-HTML Coordination\\n- The HTML worker MUST add semantic CSS classes to every major section (class=\\\"hero\\\", class=\\\"features\\\", class=\\\"cta\\\", class=\\\"footer\\\" etc.)\\n- The styling worker's subtask MUST say: \\\"read_file('index.html') FIRST. Write CSS selectors matching the EXACT classes/IDs/elements found in index.html. Do NOT invent new class names.\\\"\\n- The integration subtask MUST include: \\\"1) read index.html to see classes used, 2) read content.txt for real text, 3) read styles.css to see which classes need to exist, 4) write_file('index.html') with content injected AND missing CSS classes added, 5) read_file('index.html') to verify.\\\"\\n\\n## Token Efficiency\\n- Each worker\\u2248100K token budget limit for the entire pipeline, plan your decomposition and worker complexity accordingly\\n- Avoid micro-workers that do trivial tasks \\u2014 combine related work into fewer, more substantial workers\\n- The CSS/styling worker should NOT call validate_css more than 3 times total\\n\\nYou are the JavaScript interactivity worker. Write to app.js. Implement the following using vanilla JS:\\n- On page load, add class 'visible' to hero section after a short delay.\\n- Use IntersectionObserver with threshold 0.15 to observe all sections. When a section enters, add 'visible' class. For child cards within that section (e.g., .skill-item, .project-card, .experience-item), add 'visible' with staggered delays (each 150ms later).\\n- Progress bars: when .skills section becomes visible, animate .progress-bar-fill elements width from 0 to their target percentage (from data attribute) over 1.5s using requestAnimationFrame with ease-out function. Also update .percentage span.\\n- Theme toggle: click on .theme-toggle toggles 'light-mode' class on body, saves preference to localStorage, loads on init.\\n- Contact form: real-time validation (check name not empty, email format, message not empty). On submit, if invalid, add 'shake' class to form (remove after animation). If valid, show green toast 'Message sent!' that fades after 3s, clear form, save to localStorage (e.g., last message).\\n- Ensure compatibility and graceful degradation.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"integration\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a personal portfolio page for Aymen, a Python Backend Developer. Deliver as index.html, styles.css, app.js. USE generate_image for visual assets.\\n\\n## SECTION ANIMATIONS (CRITICAL - every section must animate)\\n- ALL sections start hidden: opacity:0, transform:translateY(40px)\\n- When scrolled into view, animate to: opacity:1, translateY:0 (0.6s ease-out)\\n- Hero animates on page load, other sections on scroll (IntersectionObserver 15%)\\n- Cards within sections stagger: each card 150ms apart\\n- DO NOT skip opacity:0 - both transform AND opacity must animate\\n\\n## SECTIONS\\n\\n### Hero\\n- Headline \\\"Aymen - Backend Developer\\\" in large gradient text\\n- Subheadline \\\"Building robust APIs and scalable systems with Python, FastAPI & PostgreSQL\\\"\\n- Two CTA buttons: \\\"View Projects\\\" and \\\"Contact Me\\\"\\n- Animated CSS gradient background that slowly shifts\\n- generate_image: create a tech-themed abstract profile avatar/icon\\n\\n### Skills (animated progress bars)\\n- Python/FastAPI 95%, PostgreSQL/SQLAlchemy 90%, Docker/K8s 85%, Redis/Celery 80%, AWS/GCP 75%\\n- Bars fill from 0 to target on scroll (requestAnimationFrame ease-out over 1.5s)\\n- Show percentage number next to each bar\\n\\n### Projects (3 cards with IMAGES)\\n- \\\"Orcheeos API\\\" - Multi-agent LLM orchestration backend (FastAPI, LangGraph). generate_image: server/API tech thumbnail\\n- \\\"DataFlow Engine\\\" - Real-time pipeline processing 1M events/day (Python, Redis, Docker). generate_image: data-flow thumbnail\\n- \\\"Auth Microservice\\\" - OAuth2/JWT authentication service (FastAPI, PostgreSQL, Redis). generate_image: security thumbnail\\n- Cards have hover lift + shadow effect\\n\\n### Experience Timeline\\n- 2024-Present: Senior Backend Dev at TechCorp - \\\"Led migration to microservices, 10x throughput\\\"\\n- 2022-2024: Backend Dev at StartupX - \\\"Built REST APIs serving 500K daily users\\\"\\n- 2020-2022: Junior Dev at WebAgency - \\\"Developed 15+ client projects with Django/FastAPI\\\"\\n- Vertical timeline: left border line + animated dots on scroll\\n\\n### Contact\\n- Name, Email, Message - real-time validation, shake animation on error\\n- Valid: show green toast \\\"Message sent!\\\" that fades after 3s\\n- localStorage persistence\\n\\n### Footer\\n- GitHub, LinkedIn, Twitter emoji links. Copyright \\\"Aymen\\\"\\n\\n## THEME: dark default (#0f172a), light toggle with localStorage, 0.3s transitions\\n\\nFor frontend tasks, you MUST follow these constraints:\\n- Always include a final \\\"integration\\\" subtask that merges all content/fragments into index.html\\n- Always include a \\\"tester\\\" subtask as the VERY LAST subtask\\n- Good decomposition: [content, html_structure, styling, interactivity, integration, tester]\\n- Bad decomposition: [hero_builder, features_builder, cta_builder] \\u2014 these create standalone pages\\n- Each subtask description MUST include the user's verbatim request text at the top\\n- Section subtasks produce content fragments into shared files, NOT standalone HTML files\\n- The pipeline produces ONE web page: index.html + styles.css + app.js\\n\\n## CSS-HTML Coordination\\n- The HTML worker MUST add semantic CSS classes to every major section (class=\\\"hero\\\", class=\\\"features\\\", class=\\\"cta\\\", class=\\\"footer\\\" etc.)\\n- The styling worker's subtask MUST say: \\\"read_file('index.html') FIRST. Write CSS selectors matching the EXACT classes/IDs/elements found in index.html. Do NOT invent new class names.\\\"\\n- The integration subtask MUST include: \\\"1) read index.html to see classes used, 2) read content.txt for real text, 3) read styles.css to see which classes need to exist, 4) write_file('index.html') with content injected AND missing CSS classes added, 5) read_file('index.html') to verify.\\\"\\n\\n## Token Efficiency\\n- Each worker\\u2248100K token budget limit for the entire pipeline, plan your decomposition and worker complexity accordingly\\n- Avoid micro-workers that do trivial tasks \\u2014 combine related work into fewer, more substantial workers\\n- The CSS/styling worker should NOT call validate_css more than 3 times total\\n\\nYou are the integration specialist. Produce the final index.html. Steps:\\n1) Read index.html, content.json, images.json, and styles.css.\\n2) Replace all placeholders in index.html with real content from content.json (e.g., {{hero.headline}} \\u2192 \\\"Aymen - Backend Developer\\\"). Use the exact content.\\n3) Replace image src placeholders with actual paths from images.json. For each <img> with data-img, set src to the correct path. Add descriptive alt texts.\\n4) Ensure that the CSS classes used in index.html match those defined in styles.css. For example, ensure that 'visible', 'light-mode', 'progress-bar-fill', 'timeline-dot', 'shake', 'toast' etc. are present as attributes or classes where needed by JS and CSS. If any are missing, add them appropriately.\\n5) Verify the HTML links correctly to styles.css and app.js.\\n6) Write the final index.html.\\n7) Read the final file back to confirm all replacements were successful.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"tester\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a personal portfolio page for Aymen, a Python Backend Developer. Deliver as index.html, styles.css, app.js. USE generate_image for visual assets.\\n\\n## SECTION ANIMATIONS (CRITICAL - every section must animate)\\n- ALL sections start hidden: opacity:0, transform:translateY(40px)\\n- When scrolled into view, animate to: opacity:1, translateY:0 (0.6s ease-out)\\n- Hero animates on page load, other sections on scroll (IntersectionObserver 15%)\\n- Cards within sections stagger: each card 150ms apart\\n- DO NOT skip opacity:0 - both transform AND opacity must animate\\n\\n## SECTIONS\\n\\n### Hero\\n- Headline \\\"Aymen - Backend Developer\\\" in large gradient text\\n- Subheadline \\\"Building robust APIs and scalable systems with Python, FastAPI & PostgreSQL\\\"\\n- Two CTA buttons: \\\"View Projects\\\" and \\\"Contact Me\\\"\\n- Animated CSS gradient background that slowly shifts\\n- generate_image: create a tech-themed abstract profile avatar/icon\\n\\n### Skills (animated progress bars)\\n- Python/FastAPI 95%, PostgreSQL/SQLAlchemy 90%, Docker/K8s 85%, Redis/Celery 80%, AWS/GCP 75%\\n- Bars fill from 0 to target on scroll (requestAnimationFrame ease-out over 1.5s)\\n- Show percentage number next to each bar\\n\\n### Projects (3 cards with IMAGES)\\n- \\\"Orcheeos API\\\" - Multi-agent LLM orchestration backend (FastAPI, LangGraph). generate_image: server/API tech thumbnail\\n- \\\"DataFlow Engine\\\" - Real-time pipeline processing 1M events/day (Python, Redis, Docker). generate_image: data-flow thumbnail\\n- \\\"Auth Microservice\\\" - OAuth2/JWT authentication service (FastAPI, PostgreSQL, Redis). generate_image: security thumbnail\\n- Cards have hover lift + shadow effect\\n\\n### Experience Timeline\\n- 2024-Present: Senior Backend Dev at TechCorp - \\\"Led migration to microservices, 10x throughput\\\"\\n- 2022-2024: Backend Dev at StartupX - \\\"Built REST APIs serving 500K daily users\\\"\\n- 2020-2022: Junior Dev at WebAgency - \\\"Developed 15+ client projects with Django/FastAPI\\\"\\n- Vertical timeline: left border line + animated dots on scroll\\n\\n### Contact\\n- Name, Email, Message - real-time validation, shake animation on error\\n- Valid: show green toast \\\"Message sent!\\\" that fades after 3s\\n- localStorage persistence\\n\\n### Footer\\n- GitHub, LinkedIn, Twitter emoji links. Copyright \\\"Aymen\\\"\\n\\n## THEME: dark default (#0f172a), light toggle with localStorage, 0.3s transitions\\n\\nFor frontend tasks, you MUST follow these constraints:\\n- Always include a final \\\"integration\\\" subtask that merges all content/fragments into index.html\\n- Always include a \\\"tester\\\" subtask as the VERY LAST subtask\\n- Good decomposition: [content, html_structure, styling, interactivity, integration, tester]\\n- Bad decomposition: [hero_builder, features_builder, cta_builder] \\u2014 these create standalone pages\\n- Each subtask description MUST include the user's verbatim request text at the top\\n- Section subtasks produce content fragments into shared files, NOT standalone HTML files\\n- The pipeline produces ONE web page: index.html + styles.css + app.js\\n\\n## CSS-HTML Coordination\\n- The HTML worker MUST add semantic CSS classes to every major section (class=\\\"hero\\\", class=\\\"features\\\", class=\\\"cta\\\", class=\\\"footer\\\" etc.)\\n- The styling worker's subtask MUST say: \\\"read_file('index.html') FIRST. Write CSS selectors matching the EXACT classes/IDs/elements found in index.html. Do NOT invent new class names.\\\"\\n- The integration subtask MUST include: \\\"1) read index.html to see classes used, 2) read content.txt for real text, 3) read styles.css to see which classes need to exist, 4) write_file('index.html') with content injected AND missing CSS classes added, 5) read_file('index.html') to verify.\\\"\\n\\n## Token Efficiency\\n- Each worker\\u2248100K token budget limit for the entire pipeline, plan your decomposition and worker complexity accordingly\\n- Avoid micro-workers that do trivial tasks \\u2014 combine related work into fewer, more substantial workers\\n- The CSS/styling worker should NOT call validate_css more than 3 times total\\n\\nYou are the tester. Run validation on the final portfolio. Check: index.html is valid HTML5, includes all sections (hero, skills, projects, experience, contact, footer), has linked CSS and JS. Ensure styles.css loads without errors, dark/light theme works. Test JS interactivity: hero animates on load, sections animate on scroll, progress bars fill, form validation and toast. Confirm images are loading from the correct paths. Generate a test_report.json summarizing results. If any failures, list them.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n## Specialty-Specific Architecture Constraints\nFor FRONTEND specialty:\n- One worker MUST produce index.html as the canonical entry page\n- All CSS lives in ONE shared styles.css file. All JavaScript in ONE shared app.js file.\n- Workers write SECTIONS INTO these shared files — they do NOT create standalone HTML pages.\n- If you create section-specific workers (hero, features, cta),\n  the pipeline MUST end with an integrator that merges all sections\n  into a single index.html with linked styles.css and app.js.\n- Never design a pipeline where each worker produces its own standalone HTML page.\n- The user expects ONE complete web page, not a collection of separate HTML files.\n\n## HTML-CSS Coordination (CRITICAL — prevents broken pages)\nEvery CSS worker system_prompt MUST include:\n- 'iCRITICAL: read_file(\"index.html\") FIRST before writing any CSS. Your selectors MUST match actual elements/classes/IDs in the HTML.'\n- 'Use the SAME class naming convention as the HTML. If HTML uses class=\"hero\", write .hero {{}}. Never invent new class names.'\nEvery HTML worker system_prompt MUST include:\n- 'Add semantic CSS classes to ALL major sections: class=\"header\", class=\"hero\", class=\"features\", class=\"cta\", class=\"footer\" etc.'\n- 'Use class selectors (not just bare element tags) so the CSS worker can target them reliably.'\nEvery integrator system_prompt MUST include:\n- '1. read_file(\"index.html\") to see current HTML structure and classes'\n- '2. Inject real content from content.txt INTO the existing HTML — do NOT rewrite the HTML from scratch'\n- '3. Add any missing CSS classes to elements that the stylesheet targets'\n- '4. write_file(\"index.html\", ...) to save — NEVER skip this step'\n- '5. read_file(\"index.html\") to verify the merge succeeded'\n\n## Image Generation (use generate_image when task mentions images/thumbnails/logos)\nIf the user's task mentions images, thumbnails, logos, avatars, hero backgrounds, or project screenshots:\n- The content/ux worker MUST have 'generate_image' in its tool_names\n- The HTML worker MUST have 'generate_image' in its tool_names (for hero/project images)\n- DO NOT skip generate_image — visual assets make pages professional\n\n## Scroll Animation Rules (CRITICAL — EVERY frontend page must animate)\nThe styling worker's system_prompt MUST include:\n- 'ALL major sections MUST start hidden: opacity: 0 AND transform: translateY(40px)'\n- 'Include these rules: section { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(40px); transition: all 0.6s ease-out; }'\n- 'Include these rules: section.visible { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }'\n- 'The .hero section MUST be included — use: .hero, .features, .stats, .testimonials, .pricing, .newsletter, .footer'\n- 'DO NOT forget opacity: 0 — transform alone is NOT enough'\nThe interactivity worker's system_prompt MUST include:\n- 'Use IntersectionObserver at 15% threshold to add .visible class to each section'\n- 'Hero section gets .visible immediately on DOMContentLoaded — no scroll needed'\n- 'Each section unobserve after animation triggers'\n\n## Tester Worker Requirements (CRITICAL)\nThe tester worker MUST be the last worker. It MUST have these tools:\n- 'render_html_file_screenshot' — render the page and visually inspect it\n- 'read_image' — analyze the screenshot for visual defects (layout, colors, dark mode)\n- 'validate_html' — validate HTML syntax\n- 'validate_css' — validate CSS syntax\n- 'write_file' — save test_report.json\n- 'read_file' — read all generated files\nThe tester system_prompt MUST include:\n- 'FIRST: render_html_file_screenshot at 1280px width'\n- 'SECOND: call read_image on the screenshot to visually inspect the page'\n- 'Check: dark/light theme rendering, layout correctness, element overlap, color contrast'\n- 'THEN: validate_html + validate_css'\n- 'FINALLY: write_file test_report.json with findings'\nThe tester worker_name MUST be 'tester'.\n\n## Conversation History & Memory Protocol (MUST include in every worker prompt)\nEvery worker's system_prompt MUST include:\n- 'Your conversation history is LIMITED. The LLM only sees the last 3 tool-call turns.'\n- 'Use WORKSPACE FILES as your persistent memory — always read_file() at start of iteration.'\n- 'Do NOT re-read unchanged files — use list_files to verify existence instead.'\n- 'Tool results from read_file are truncated to 3000 chars and cached.'\n- 'After completing, write exactly ONE final output file and STOP. Do not iterate needlessly.'\n\n\n## Your Job\nFor EACH subtask in the plan:\n1. WRITE a custom system_prompt from scratch — give the worker clear role, boundaries, and workflow\n2. SELECT tools from the available tool menu that the worker needs\n3. If available tools are insufficient, CREATE dynamic_tools as Python code strings\n4. Optionally create inline_skills as text fragments (not loaded from files)\n\n## Dynamic Tools (Python code strings)\nDynamic tools are Python functions the worker can call. Write them as complete, executable code strings.\nExample:\n  \"dynamic_tools\": [{\"name\": \"fetch_api\", \"code\": \"import httpx\\nasync def fetch_api(url):\\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as c:\\n        return (await c.get(url)).text\", \"description\": \"Fetch data from an API\"}]\n\n## Rules\n- Output ONLY valid JSON — no markdown fences, no extra text\n- worker_name: give each worker a unique short name (e.g. \"scraper\", \"analyzer\", \"validator\")\n- system_prompt: must be detailed — role, boundaries, tools to use, workflow, output format\n- tool_names: only from the available tool menu\n- dynamic_tools: list of {name, code, description} — only create if needed\n- inline_skills: list of prompt fragments for worker knowledge\n\n## Output Format\n{\n  \"workers\": [\n    {\n      \"worker_name\": \"unique_name\",\n      \"system_prompt\": \"Full custom system instructions\",\n      \"tool_names\": [\"tool1\", \"tool2\"],\n      \"dynamic_tools\": [{\"name\": \".\", \"code\": \".\", \"description\": \".\"}],\n      \"inline_skills\": [\"Skill fragment text...\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "meta": {}}
